<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Hello Kitty, is a fictional character produced by the Japanese company Sanrio, first designed by Ikuko Shimizu. Her first appearance on an item, a vinyl coin purse, was introduced in Japan in 1974 and brought to the United States in 1976.
                  <br><br>The character is portrayed as a female white cat with a red bow and no drawn mouth. She lives in London, England with her parents and twin sister.
                  <br><br>The Hello Kitty line has since developed licensing arrangements worth more than $1 billion a year in sales. Examples of products depicting the character include dolls, stickers, greeting cards, clothes, accessories, school supplies, dishes and home appliances. Hello Kitty has an official theme park, Sanrio Puroland, which opened in 1990.
                  <br><br>In Kids Station Hello Kitty to Album Nikki o Tsukuri Masho! The player will travel with Helloy Kitty to different countries around the World with Hello Kitty and play different minigames .
                  <br><br>The mini games are really different: In one of them the player cook and then serve the food, in other Kitty has to grab hats in Mexico, she can make Sky slalom in Canada or play soccer in Brasil, etc.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>A fun software that allows first whenever visiting and chatting with Kitty Kids appeared on the PS! Features such as full albums, and fun mini-games! Through drawing, imagination and organization ability, thinking and cultivate a sense of color and can be fun to learn through play and educational decisions, and an English accent sounds.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Fantasy & Educational themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
